replies.text:
@bikerfirefarter7280 Good idea! 
I am far from being an expert in this, but wouldn't that method strip electrons and not add them? 
Is that the intention?

@totherarf The intention is to create radicals and other intermediates such as O and OH (and maybe others) that will influence things like unburned hydrocarbons and CO to react to form H2O and CO2, maybe even encourage micro-carbon particles to 'burn'. The idea is to provide some effects that will replace/reduce the use of expensive 'platinum' group catalysts.
'Cats' are particularly ineffective until they get up to temperature anyway, and that can take a surprisingly long time, so not much use on short trips.
And if we can reduce/replace the metals Scrotes wont have reason to nick them.  ;-)
